copyHolder.mainCopy: The first fixture of Euro 2016 sees the hosts take on Romania

The 24 teams have been divided into six groups with the top two from each section – as well as the four best third-placed teams – to progress to the knockout stage. The games will be played in 10 different stadiums across France
The second phase of the tournament will start on 25 June with matches in Lens, Paris and Saint-Étienne
The 10 venues for the 2016 Euros stretch from Lille in the north to Marseille in the south. Stade de France has the biggest capacity at 80,000 with the venue in Toulouse the smallest at 33,000
